Major changes compared to last set of concepts:
• Max. 3 possible actions at any one time for each bubble (close bubble, open app, expand OR show actions)
• Notification groups are stacks, which expand with an animation
• Expanded groups obscure the rest of the list
• Messaging/Email notification can have rounded avatars on the right
• Visual tweaks, including increased padding and border radii, and larger font size for notification body text

flowRoot.flowPara: The most recent notification in the stack has its actions expanded by default, others can be revealed manually, same as with non-grouped top level notifications.
The ellipsis icon indicates whether a bubble has actions.
Clicking the bottom 30px or so of the cards reveals the actions.

flowRoot.flowPara: The close button is revealed if the mouse cursor hovers anywhere over a bubble.
Bubbles can also be dismissed via horizontal swipe in either direction on touchpads and touchscreens.
Revealing Close Button

When expanding a stack of bubbles, the cards fan out with a semantic animation. Other notifications move up/down to make room, and fade out to indicate that they're no longer interactive. Clicking anywhere above or below the expanded cards (or the back button at the top) collapses the stack.

flowRoot.flowPara: When an app has multiple bubbles, only the most recent one is visible, as the top item of a stack of cards.

At the bottom of this card there's a label indicating how many other notifications are in the stack, which can be clicked to expand the stack. The click target goes a bit beyond that, and also includes the visible parts of the other cards below.
